    <p class="lead">I'm an Aussie web developer based in Brisbane. I have a Software Engineering degree, and more importantly, about 15 years of industry experience.</p>
    <p>I specialise in modern Javascript & NodeJS development, but also have experience with a wide range of web technologies, and always love to learn new ones.  See skills</p>

    <h2>Non Technical</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Clear, effective communicator</li>
        <li>Friendly, easy going personality</li>
        <li>Pragmatic, "best tool for the job" mentality</li>
        <li>Ability to work with minimal direction and read and understand existing codebases independently</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Technical</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Knowledge of different programming languages and paradigms</li>
        <li>Understanding of SOLID software development principles and design patterns</li>
        <li>Extensive experience with HTTP, REST and Web Applications in general</li>
        <li>Extensive experience with version control (git and github, preferably)</li>
        <li>Ability to use a debugger to track down the source of an issue</li>
        <li>Focus on unit testing / test driven development</li>
        <li>Meticulous attention to detail and documentation. Markdown for life!</li>
        <li>Experience with different databases, ORMs, NoSQL document stores, search indices, etc</li>
        <li>Experience with security (at least a basic understanding of XSS, CSRF &amp; SQL Injection)</li>
        <li>Experience with package management / build processes / continuous integration / containerisation</li>
        <li>Experience dealing with high volume traffic sites and producing scalable, robust architectures</li>
        <li>Experience with "12 Factor App"</li>
    </ul>

